HEADWORD: Epiphyte
<hw>Ep"i*phyte</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>'epi`</grk> upon + <grk>fyto`n</grk> plant, <?/ to grow: cf. F.
<ets>⟦eacute⟧piphyte</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>An
air plant which grows on other plants, but does not derive its
nourishment from them. See <er>Air plant</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A vegetable parasite growing on
the surface of the body.</def></p>

